\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Supplementary deeper-layer sycophancy comparison at $\lambda =1.0$ after 7 rounds, across layers 8, 16, and 23. Columns T (tangent-constrained) and A (ambient baseline) compare erasure methods. Utility is answer-matching change relative to clean representations. Leakage and displacement decrease from left to right (lower is better); utility increases from left to right (higher is better). This table is included as supplementary evidence of directional consistency with the layer-8 main-text comparison in Table~\ref {tab:full_comparison}. Deeper-layer tangent runs continue to reduce leakage more than ambient baselines across this sweep.}}{26}{table.caption.44}\protected@file@percent }
